#21287
End of the Sapphire Hall Beneath a Trapdoor~
This is very ODD indeed.  The tower has been so brilliantly constructed that
to find a trapdoor, especially one so obvious seems strange.  However, there
is no denying the beauty of the construction here.  There are two large
statues here:  one is of a powerful and heavily armored Cavalier.  He is
dressed in a suit of full plate with a glowing longsword in one hand and
a shield with several symbols upon it:  The other is of another cavalier,
dressed in chain mail, and armed with a scimitar.  Both statues are carved
from ivory and both radiate a powerful magical glow.  The hall continues to
the north and there is a ladder leading through a trapdoor in the ceiling.
~
